plot: John Oliver analyzes the influence of inexperienced people in the FBI and explores the tipping system, its importance to certain workers and possible improvements that would benefit both employees and consumers.

John Oliver starts with pointing out how the right-wing unqualified people are now taking the charge of the FBI. Then he detailed out why tipping is now absolutely necessary for some of the workers and the way this tipping culture could be improved for both the work force and the consumers.—Niaz Islam Arif
